From ed17548a1211817e473f5c483eec8ef2d397b822 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petlozu Pravareshwar <petlozup@nvidia.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Apr 2024 06:53:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 22/95] NVIDIA: SAUCE: soc/tegra: pmc: Re-organize PMC driver
 APIs

BugLink: https://bugs.launchpad.net/bugs/2072591

Re-organize PMC driver APIs to pass around struct tegra_pmc pointer
as much as possible instead of using the global variable. Also move
PMC structure definitions from driver file to the PMC header file.

http://nvbugs/4470933

Upstream-Status: Backport
Signed-off-by: Petlozu Pravareshwar <petlozup@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Bitan Biswas <bbiswas@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Laxman Dewangan <ldewangan@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Jacob Martin <jacob.martin@canonical.com>
Acked-by: Noah Wager <noah.wager@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Noah Wager <noah.wager@canonical.com>
(cherry picked from commit bf92861fb7c4dc20dc398720b5fda82ea4f880a5)
Signed-off-by: Matt Madison <matt@madison.systems>
